          bigtophero
"></div><p> <em>《华尔街日报》新专题的第一期<em>，高管们讨论了他们赖以保持领先地位的应用程序。</em></em></p><p> Ali Ghodsi 是 Databricks 的联合创始人兼首席执行官，Databricks 是一家总部位于旧金山的科技公司，向公司出租分析、人工智能和其他基于云的软件。他平均每天还要花几个小时玩手机。戈德西最近与《华尔街日报》分享了他自己的分析，以深入了解他在任何一天的运作方式。以下是他最常用的应用程序： </p><div class="media-object scope-web|mobileapps
          edgetoedge
"><iframe width="300" height="300" src="https://graphics.wsj.com/dynamic-inset-iframer/?url=https://asset.wsj.net/wsjnewsgraphics/projects/narrator/48743287-9602-45ca-a20c-e02c480ad1d1.json" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></iframe></div><p>写信给 Corrie Driebusch，邮箱为<a href="mailto:corrie.driebusch@dowjones.com" target="_blank" class="icon ">corrie.driebusch@dowjones.com</a></p></section></div></main></div> ]]>;</description><pubDate> Sat, 29 Jul 2023 04:00:00 GMT</pubDate><guid ispermalink="false"> https://www.wsj.com/articles/ali-ghodsi-databricks-phone-3cec6486</guid><link/> https://www.wsj.com/articles/ali-ghodsi-databricks-phone-3cec6486<author><![CDATA[Corrie Driebusch]]></author><category>摄影委托</category><category>世杰交易所</category><category>计算机/消费电子产品</category><category>软件</category><category>应用软件</category><category>计算</category><category>移动应用软件</category><category>技术</category><category>管理</category><category>企业/行业新闻</category><category>高层管理人员</category><category>内容类型</category><category>法激活过滤器</category><category>会展行业新闻过滤器</category><category>SYND</category><category>华尔街日报-PRO-WSJ.com</category><category>阿里·戈德西</category><category>管理</category><category>公司的</category><category>行业新闻</category><category>高层管理人员</category><category>内容类型</category><category>法蒂瓦过滤器</category><category>会展行业新闻过滤器</category><category>电脑</category><category>消费类电子产品</category><category>软件</category><category>应用软件</category><category>计算</category><category>移动应用软件</category><category>技术</category></item><item><title><![CDATA[Joe and Hunter: President Ignores Perils, Embraces Scandal-Plagued Son]]></title><description><![CDATA[<div> Some presidential allies worry that Hunter Biden&#39;s prominent appearances are a liability <figure><img src="https://images.wsj.net/im-825643/?width=1278&amp;size=1" alt="拜登总统和亨特·拜登四月在白宫举行复活节滚彩蛋活动。" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"><figcaption> President Biden and Hunter Biden at the White House Easter Egg Roll in April. EVELYN HOCKSTEIN/REUTERS <span>EVELYN HOCKSTEIN/REUTERS</span> </figcaption></figure><!-- data-module-name="article.app/lib/module/wsj/breadcrumbs" --><main id="main" role="main"><div class="wsj-article-headline-wrap crawler"></div><div class="articleLead" itemprop="articleLead" data-sbid="WP-WSJ-0001079998"></div><div class="articleBody" data-sbid="WP-WSJ-0001079998"><div class="clearfix bylineWrap"><div class="byline"> By <span class="author" itemprop="name"><a href="https://www.wsj.com/news/author/annie-linskey" itemprop="url" rel="author">Annie Linskey</a></span></div><time class="timestamp article__timestamp flexbox__flex--1">更新于 2023 年 7 月 29 日中午 12:00（东部时间） </time></div><div subscriptions-actions="" subscriptions-display="NOT data.noSharing"><div class="share-bar"><amp-social-share type="system" width="72" height="24" data-param-url="https://www.wsj.com/articles/joe-and-hunter-biden-ignores-political-perils-and-embraces-scandal-plagued-son-f105aee2"></amp-social-share></div></div><section subscriptions-section="content"><div class="media-object scope-web|mobileapps
          bigtophero
"></div><p> WASHINGTON—Schmoozing at a state dinner for the Indian prime minister. Strolling past a bank of cameras before taking off in Marine One for Camp David. Waving to crowds from the White House balcony on the Fourth of July.</p><p> These are all pieces of presidential theater. But in each instance, the actor is Hunter Biden, not his father, Joe, though the president is close at hand. Taken together, they capture how closely and squarely in the spotlight President Biden has kept his <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/hunter-biden-plea-deal-limbo-republicans-749b5187?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">scandal-plagued son</a> .</p><p> That proximity worries some presidential allies who privately say that parading Hunter Biden around serves as a reminder of the younger Biden&#39;s poor judgment and past attempts <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/hunter-bidens-family-name-aided-deals-with-foreign-tycoons-11608682462?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">to monetize his political connections</a> as House Republicans step up their investigation into whether son and father inappropriately profited from the family&#39;s power.</p><p> The negative spotlight settled again on the younger Biden this past week when a judge refused to accept a <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/hunter-biden-plea-deal-in-jeopardy-ff556d70?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">plea deal</a> that would have allowed him to acknowledge guilt on misdemeanor tax charges and likely avoid prison time, as well as skirting a gun charge. After prosecutors and defense attorneys disagreed over whether Hunter Biden could face additional charges, the judge gave them 30 days to provide more information.</p><p> Several people close to the president explain his decision to keep Hunter Biden close as stemming from a fatherly concern for a son with a long history of substance abuse. They note that the president, like the parents of many people who have struggled with addiction, is always worried about the potential for a relapse. They also say that the president frequently invites his extended family on trips and to White House events. </p><div class="media-object scope-
          inline
"><div class="media-object-video"><div class="wsj-media-summary clearfix"><div class="strap-container"><h4 class="strap" itemprop="description"></h4></div></div><iframe width="400" height="225" src="https://video-api.wsj.com/api-video/player/v3/iframe.html?guid=0B3DB0F9-BB08-44C5-9D27-7C99347D4C8F&amp;height=225&amp;width=400&amp;plid=video_amp&amp;chainVideos=true&amp;parentUrl=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.wsj.com%2Famp%2Farticles%2Fjoe-and-hunter-biden-ignores-political-perils-and-embraces-scandal-plagued-son-f105aee2&amp;a=a" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></iframe><p class="imageCaption"> Hunter Biden pleaded not guilty to misdemeanor tax charges after a federal judge deferred a planned guilty plea deal. Photo: Anna Moneymaker/Getty Images<span class="imageCredit">
        
        
        </span></p></div></div><p>Given the deep bond between the father and son, aides said that they loathe bringing up concerns regarding Hunter Biden and that few staff members are willing to do so.</p><p> “If the world was controlled by political consultants, I don&#39;t think [President Biden] would do some of the things he&#39;s done,” said David Axelrod, <strong>&nbsp;</strong> who was Barack Obama&#39;s top political strategist. “But he&#39;s acting as a father, not a candidate, and signaling his unshakable loyalty to his son.”</p><p> Republicans have been more blunt: “There&#39;s a number of places I probably would not have had invited him to,” House Speaker Kevin McCarthy (R., Calif.) said in an interview. And on Fox News this past week, McCarthy signaled that the House is on a clear course to pursuing an impeachment case against President Biden, citing claims of corruption tied to his son&#39;s overseas business dealings, though the speaker later tempered those comments.</p><p> Hunter Biden also accompanied his father on a trip to Ireland earlier this year, traveling by Air Force One and appearing with the president at several stops. He also attended a state dinner for French President Emmanuel Macron.</p><p> Some have seized on Hunter Biden&#39;s appearance at a more recent state dinner held at the White House for Narendra Modi, the Indian prime minister. It was attended by Attorney General Merrick Garland,</p> and it happened to be two days after the Justice Department came to the tentative deal that collapsed. Republicans have denounced the accord as <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/did-hunter-biden-get-a-sweetheart-deal-prosecutors-weigh-in-2dc8656e?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">a sweetheart deal</a> .<p></p><p> Asked the following day about Hunter Biden&#39;s attendance at the state dinner, White House press secretary Karine Jean-Pierre said: “I&#39;m just not going to get into family discussion—personal family discussion.” </p><div class="media-object scope-
          bleed
"><figure class="media-object-image img-bleed"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="1260" height="840" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-825484?width=1260&amp;height=840" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent"> Hunter Biden greeting a guest at a White House state dinner for the Indian prime minister last month.</p><p class="imageCredit"> Photo: ELIZABETH FRANTZ/REUTERS</p></figcaption></figure></div><p> There is a limit to the bond. Jean-Pierre on Thursday said “no” when asked if there was <a href="https://www.whitehouse.gov/briefing-room/press-briefings/2023/07/27/press-briefing-by-press-secretary-karine-jean-pierre-46/" target="_blank" class="icon none" rel="noopener">any possibility</a> that the president would pardon his son.</p><p> Hunter Biden has written extensively about his relationship with his father, crediting him with saving his life when, as vice president, <a href="https://www.wsj.com/topics/person/joe-biden">Joe Biden</a> ,</p> plus a slimmed-down security detail, showed up at his adult son&#39;s Washington apartment and insisted he get help for his addiction. “He never abandoned me, never shunned me, never judged me, no matter how bad things got,” Hunter Biden wrote in his 2021 memoir. “As busy as Dad always was, he never, ever gave up on me.”<p></p><p> In a section of the book focused on his decision to join the board of Burisma, the Ukrainian energy company, Hunter Biden wrote that he has apologized repeatedly for causing his father so many political headaches. “He responded by saying how sorry he was for putting me on the spot, for bringing so much heat onto me,” Hunter Biden wrote. “That&#39;s the biggest political debate my dad and I had for months: Who should apologize to whom?”</p><p> House GOP investigators are seeking to tie President Biden to Hunter Biden&#39;s work overseas including in Ukraine and China. The White House has repeatedly said the president wasn&#39;t involved in his son&#39;s businesses, and Hunter Biden has said that he had a longstanding agreement not to talk about deals with his father. None of The Wall Street Journal&#39;s reporting has found that Joe Biden benefited from his son&#39;s business activities.</p><p> Recent days showed what is in store for the GOP&#39;s attacks. Rep. Marjorie Taylor Greene (R., Ga.) displayed during a committee hearing explicit photos of Hunter Biden that she said came from his laptop, in an unsubstantiated attempt to accuse him of sex trafficking. </p><div class="media-object scope-
          inline
"><figure class="media-object-image img-inline"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="700" height="466" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-825483?width=700&amp;height=466" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent"> Rep. Marjorie Taylor Greene preparing to display explicit images at a committee hearing in mid-July.</p><p class="imageCredit"> Photo: Stephanie Scarbrough/Associated Press</p></figcaption></figure></div><p> Sen.</p> Chuck Grassley (R., Iowa) released a Federal Bureau of Investigation document in which Hunter Biden was described by an informant as “not smart” and the alleged recipient of millions of dollars in payments in exchange for his political connections. Democrats criticized the document&#39;s release and said many of its claims had been previously debunked.<p></p><p> On Monday, Hunter Biden&#39;s former business associate, Devon Archer, is set to go before the House Committee on Oversight and Accountability for a transcribed interview in which GOP investigators are expected to press him on business deals that involved Hunter Biden and other family members. Among other business connections, the pair served together on the board of Burisma.</p><p> The president has repeatedly said he is proud of his son and supports his efforts to turn his life around. Beyond Hunter Biden&#39;s efforts to move past his addiction problems, the two share a bond forged by a 1972 car accident that killed Joe Biden&#39;s first wife and daughter. His two young sons, Hunter and Beau, survived the crash. Beau Biden died in 2015 of brain cancer, leaving the president with one surviving son who at the time seemed to be losing his yearslong battle with addiction.</p><p> White House aides and allies of the president say they have little concern over the potential for Hunter Biden&#39;s woes to drag down Biden&#39;s approval rating, which has been hovering <a href="https://projects.fivethirtyeight.com/biden-approval-rating/" target="_blank" class="icon none" rel="noopener">just over 40%</a> for months. They add that recent elections show that Hunter Biden has had little impact on the president with independent voters and that most Democrats pay little attention to the twists and turns of GOP investigations into his past. </p><div class="media-object scope-
          bleed
"><figure class="media-object-image img-bleed"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="1260" height="771" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-825485?width=1260&amp;height=771" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent"> Jill Biden with Beau Biden and Hunter Biden before the start of the vice presidential debate in Kentucky in 2012.</p><p class="imageCredit"> Photo: Pablo Martinez Monsivais/Associated Press</p></figcaption></figure></div><p> “They tried and tried and tried to make the Biden family an issue in 2020—and lost,” said Sen. Chris Coons (D., Del.),a national co-chair of Biden&#39;s re-election campaign. “They tried again harder to make Hunter in particular an issue in 2022,” he added, saying the result was a poor showing in the midterms. “So by all means, try again,” he said.</p><p> Some Republicans tread carefully on matters relating to the president&#39;s son. “One thing you never heard me do is get overly critical about his defense of Hunter,” Sen. Kevin Cramer (R., ND) said about President Biden. “I&#39;ve never faulted him for his love for his son, his expressions of support.” Cramer&#39;s adult son struggled with addiction and died in 2018 after he was hospitalized for liver and kidney failure.</p><p> The Bidens&#39; emphasis on the importance of family put pressure on the president to acknowledge that he <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/biden-acknowledges-hunters-daughter-for-the-first-time-9ea6f365?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">has a seventh grandchild</a> , a young girl in Arkansas whom Hunter Biden says he fathered while in the throes of drug addiction. After weeks of speculation, President Biden and first lady Jill Biden said in a statement Friday that the girl, Navy Joan Roberts, is a family member.<br><br> “Our son Hunter and Navy&#39;s mother, Lunden, are working together to foster a relationship that is in the best interests of their daughter, preserving her privacy as much as possible going forward,” the Bidens said in the statement, referring to Lunden Roberts. “This is not a political issue, it&#39;s a family matter,” according to the statement. “Jill and I only want what is best for all of our grandchildren, including Navy,” the statement added. </p><div class="media-object scope-
          bleed
"><figure class="media-object-image img-bleed"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="1260" height="840" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-825634?width=1260&amp;height=840" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent"> President Biden, first lady Jill Biden and family members watching Fourth of July fireworks earlier this month.</p><p class="imageCredit"> Photo: Ting Shen/Press Pool</p></figcaption></figure></div><p> House Republicans, who gained subpoena power when they won the majority in the midterms, are moving toward requiring testimony from allies of Hunter Biden and are seeking the names of collectors who purchased his artwork and the amount paid for the paintings. In recent years, Hunter Biden has pursued an art career and is selling paintings through a <a href="https://bergesgallery.com/our-artists/hunter-biden" target="_blank" class="icon none" rel="noopener">New York art gallery</a> . Asking prices have been as high as $500,000.</p><p> Republicans, and some ethics lawyers, have raised questions about whether the art sales could become an avenue for supporters of the president to funnel money to his family. With input from the White House counsel&#39;s office, Hunter Biden and his gallery devised a blind purchasing system. The gallery sets prices, handles sales and doesn&#39;t disclose names to Hunter Biden, according to Abbe Lowell, one of Hunter Biden&#39;s lawyers.</p><p> As these fights gear up, those close to the White House expect a more robust response from Hunter Biden than during the 2020 campaign, where he played a minimal role. “He&#39;s not going to sit back and passively take the smears, attacks and lies from certain Republicans in their glass houses,” said Michael LaRosa, a former aide to Jill Biden. <strong>&nbsp;</strong> “You&#39;ll eventually see and hear a more outspoken Hunter Biden fight back this time around.”</p><p class="articleTagLine"> —Lindsay Wise, Jack Gillum and Simon J. Levien contributed to this article.</p><p> Write to Annie Linskey at <a href="mailto:annie.linskey@wsj.com" target="_blank" class="icon ">annie.linskey@wsj.com</a></p></section></div></main></div> ]]>;</description><pubDate> Sat, 29 Jul 2023 04:00:00 GMT</pubDate><guid ispermalink="false"> https://www.wsj.com/articles/joe-and-hunter-biden-ignores-political-perils-and-embraces-scandal-plagued-son-f105aee2</guid><link/> https://www.wsj.com/articles/joe-and-hunter-biden-ignores-political-perils-and-embraces-scandal-plagued-son-f105aee2<author><![CDATA[Annie Linskey]]></author><category>政治/一般新闻</category><category>政治/国际关系</category><category>国内政治</category><category>SYND</category><category>华尔街日报-PRO-WSJ.com</category><category> Hunter Biden</category><category> Joe Biden</category><category>政治的</category><category>一般新闻</category><category>政治</category><category>国际关系</category><category>国内政治</category></item><item><title><![CDATA[How Netflix’s Algorithms and Tech Feed Its Success]]></title><description><![CDATA[<div>有关谁观看什么内容以及观看时长的数据会影响从推荐到剧集续订的一切<figure><img src="https://images.wsj.net/im-824171/?width=1278&amp;size=1" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"><figcaption>纳迪亚·拉迪克<span>纳迪亚·拉迪克</span></figcaption></figure><!-- data-module-name="article.app/lib/module/wsj/breadcrumbs" --><main id="main" role="main"><div class="wsj-article-headline-wrap crawler"></div><div class="articleLead" itemprop="articleLead" data-sbid="WP-WSJ-0001093740"></div><div class="articleBody" data-sbid="WP-WSJ-0001093740"><div class="clearfix bylineWrap"><div class="columnist_mini"> <a href="https://www.wsj.com/news/author/christopher-mims"><img width="45" height="45" src="https://si.wsj.net/public/resources/images/BN-CW279_mims_A_20140520065912.jpg" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></a></div><div class="byline"> <span class="author" itemprop="name"><a href="https://www.wsj.com/news/author/christopher-mims" itemprop="url" rel="author">克里斯托弗·米姆斯</a></span></div><time class="timestamp article__timestamp flexbox__flex--1">美国东部时间 2023 年 7 月 28 日晚上 9:00 </time></div><div subscriptions-actions="" subscriptions-display="NOT data.noSharing"><div class="share-bar"><amp-social-share type="system" width="72" height="24" data-param-url="https://www.wsj.com/articles/how-netflixs-algorithms-and-tech-feed-its-success-90632b92"></amp-social-share></div></div><section subscriptions-section="content"><div class="media-object scope-web|mobileapps
          bigtophero
"></div><p>几十年来， <a href="https://www.wsj.com/market-data/quotes/NFLX" class="company-name">Netflix</a>一直将其定位为一家恰好分发娱乐内容的科技公司，而该公司的高管最近试图将这家流媒体巨头重塑为一家恰好依赖科技的娱乐公司。</p><p>但不要被愚弄了：Netflix 用于收集和分析数据的专有技术仍然是该公司成功的关键。这些数据反过来又被用来决定制作哪些节目和电影、是否续订以及是否通过该公司著名的推荐算法与任何特定观众分享。</p><p>无论内容是新的原创内容（例如“女王的弃兵”、“鱿鱼游戏”和“金钱抢劫”），还是现有系列的一部分（例如“夏洛特女王：布里奇顿的故事”、“吉尔莫女孩”），情况都是如此。 ” 的复兴或后续几季的热门节目，例如“怪奇物语”。</p><p> Netflix 发言人表示，Netflix 已经私下与内容制作者分享了部分数据，并以每周公开的前 10 名名单的形式分享了这些数据。根据好莱坞作家和演员同时罢工的情况，该公司及其众多模仿者可能不得不分享更多。 </p><div class="media-object scope-web|mobileapps
          wrap
"><img width="600" height="800" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-825761?width=600" alt="不明确的" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><p>这是因为，在流媒体时代，回答演员和编剧应如何获得报酬的问题取决于这些数据，以及公司如何使用它来<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/netflix-seeks-ways-to-get-subscribers-to-return-after-visits-decline-11666032658?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">计算</a>节目是否是一项良好的投资。</p><h3><strong>数据作为劳资谈判的筹码</strong></h3><p>当合同谈判中出现剩余问题时，例如当前好莱坞罢工的核心问题，真正处于危险之中的是数据以及谁拥有这些数据，迈克尔·韦恩（Michael Wayne）说，他是该大学媒体和创意产业助理教授。鹿特丹伊拉斯姆斯大学。</p><p>美国作家协会和演员工会 SAG-Aftra 没有回应置评请求。</p><p>韦恩提到了 Netflix 的第一部大型原创剧集《纸牌屋》。即使在推出 10 年后，它对公司仍然具有价值，但具体有多大尚不清楚。</p><p> “只要为 Netflix 制作内容的人不知道自己的劳动价值，Netflix 在谈判桌上就有优势，”韦恩说。 “数据是这一切的核心。”</p><p>根据 Netflix 发言人的说法，以及 Netflix 在 2019 年致英国议会委员会的<a href="http://data.parliament.uk/writtenevidence/committeeevidence.svc/evidencedocument/communications-committee/public-service-broadcasting-in-the-age-of-video-on-demand/written/104558.html" target="_blank" class="icon none">一封信中</a>，Netflix 在过去几年中开始与制片人分享更多数据。这些数据包括有多少人在前七年开始观看一部连续剧或电影以及服务的 28 天，以及有多少人在这段时间内完成了服务。</p><p> Netflix 还推出了一项计划，允许<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/netflix-to-let-tens-of-thousands-of-subscribers-preview-content-11669851681?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">数以万计的订阅者对某些影片提供早期反馈</a>，希望能够鼓励这些影片的创作者对其进行修改，以适应观众的口味。</p><p>好莱坞人才可能希望改变这种状况。但目前的现实是，除了这些有限的披露之外，Netflix 没有动力对其专有的内部数据保持透明，芝加哥大学计算机科学副教授 Marshini Chetty 表示，他研究了该公司如何收集数据。</p><h3> Netflix的数据优势</h3><p>Netflix 使用数据的能力帮助其在流媒体游戏中利用原创内容留住订阅者，而无需花费大量资金。该<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/netflix-nflx-q2-earnings-report-2023-92a620c8?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">公司本月表示，</a>最近一个季度的订阅用户数量增加了 590 万，利润也有所增长。它赞扬了对密码共享的打击，还吹嘘说它在 2023 年的前 25 周中除了其中一周外，在美国的原创流媒体剧集中一直排名第一。相比之下，</p><a href="https://www.wsj.com/market-data/quotes/DIS" class="company-name">迪士尼</a>和其他<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/tvs-golden-era-proved-costly-to-streamers-87353c61?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">竞争对手在流媒体领域一直在亏损</a>。<p></p><p>加利福尼亚州最近的一项法律让我们得以一窥 Netflix 的数据收集情况，以及它如何利用这些数据在与流媒体竞争对手和人才谈判中获得优势。 </p><div class="media-object scope-web|mobileapps
          wrap
"><div class="media-object-rich-text"><h4>更多关键词</h4><ul class="articleList"><li><a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/exotic-new-silicon-based-speakers-are-coming-to-next-generation-earbuds-ee99b76b?mod=article_relatedinline" target="_blank" class="icon none">异国情调的新型硅基扬声器即将应用于下一代耳塞</a></li><li><a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/heres-how-twitter-could-become-irrelevant-b2b027af?mod=article_relatedinline" target="_blank" class="icon none">Twitter 可能会变得无关紧要</a></li><li><a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/ai-jobs-replace-tech-workers-8f3dc92?mod=article_relatedinline" target="_blank" class="icon none">人工智能会给你的工作带来什么？看看它已经对程序员做了什么</a></li><li><a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/pandemic-habits-shopping-restaurants-delivery-exercise-payments-a2dba53e?mod=article_relatedinline" target="_blank" class="icon none">这些大流行时代的习惯不会消失</a></li></ul></div></div><p><a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/businesses-across-the-board-scramble-to-comply-with-california-data-privacy-law-11567947602?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">2020 年生效的</a>《加州消费者隐私法》要求公司应要求向客户提供<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/businesses-across-the-board-scramble-to-comply-with-california-data-privacy-law-11567947602?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">其所掌握的有关客户的数据</a>。计算机科学博士布伦南·沙夫纳 (Brennan Schaffner) 表示，与 Netflix 合作揭示的数据具有令人惊讶的粒度。芝加哥大学的学生。</p><p>沙夫纳说，这些数据包括“自创建帐户以来您所参与的每一条内容的详细记录”，包括您观看的时间、观看时所在的位置以及使用的设备。 Netflix 还对您最初观看某些内容的原因有着前所未有的洞察力，其形式是详细记录您如何浏览服务菜单以及您点击的内容。</p><p> Netflix<a href="https://help.netflix.com/en/node/100639" target="_blank" class="icon none">解释说</a>，这些数据为其推荐算法提供动力。该公司<a href="http://techblog.netflix.com/2016/04/its-all-about-testing-netflix.html" target="_blank" class="icon none">在过去有关如何测试不同版本的预览、缩略图和其他内容的讨论中也提到了这些数据</a>。</p><h3>数据如何塑造内容</h3><p>了解 Netflix 如何使用数据的一个窗口是查看该公司如何决定更新哪些内容。</p><p>收集媒体和娱乐数据的分析公司 Ampere 的高级分析师奥利维亚·迪恩 (Olivia Deane) 表示，传统广播或有线网络上的节目平均更新六季。</p><p>然而，在 Netflix，节目通常只会续订总共三季。她补充道，至少从 2020 年开始就是如此，尽管你预计这个数字会随着时间的推移而上升。</p><p>迪恩说，这表明第三季之后的作品在吸引和留住订户方面的效用有限。 （可以肯定的是，Netflix 确实有一些长篇连续剧——《大嘴巴》已经续订到第八季。）</p><p> Netflix 对剧本节目的持续承诺——上个季度，剧本节目占 Netflix 决定续订的节目的三分之二——表明该公司发现他们在吸引和留住订户方面的投资得到了回报。 </p><div class="media-object scope-web|mobileapps
          inline
"><div class="wsj-article-pullquote article__inset__pullquote "><p class="pullquote-content article__inset__pullquote__quote"> <span class="l-qt article__inset__pullquote__mark--left">“</span> Netflix 拥有您在该服务上观看过的每部电影或节目的详细数据，包括您所在的位置、您使用的设备以及您如何导航菜单来访问它们。 <span class="r-qt article__inset__pullquote__mark--right">”</span></p></div></div><p>鉴于有脚本标题的制作成本远高于真人秀和纪录片等无脚本标题，这表明 Netflix 在数据方面的优势（该公司表示，这使其更有信心观众会观看该公司的内容）继续获得回报。</p><p> Ampere 的迪恩表示，《怪奇物语》是 Netflix 内容策略的一个典型例子。首先，由于Netflix对观众口味的数据驱动洞察，Netflix在这种昂贵的脚本节目上取得了相当大的成功。事实上，该剧只有四个季节。 （它的创作者表示希望创建第五个，但尚未确定发布日期。）</p><p> Netflix 有能力跟踪个人订阅者，以及他们何时流失（即<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/streaming-data-netflix-hbo-disney-hulu-11643560207?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">取消订阅</a>），而这些数据向 Ampere 的分析师表明，稳定供应引人注目的新节目既可以吸引并留住订阅者，但订阅者的回报却在递减。甚至继续喜爱的特许经营权。</p><p> Netflix 的内容主管贝拉·巴贾里亚 (Bela Bajaria) 在<a href="https://47annualuclaentertainmentsymposium.com/day-3/" target="_blank" class="icon none">6 月份的加州大学洛杉矶分校娱乐研讨会上发表讲话</a>时表示，“算法并不能决定我们制作什么。”</p><p> “没有一种算法可能会说，你知道什么是个好主意吗？一部关于女人下棋的时代剧，”她补充道，指的是获奖剧集《皇后弃兵》。</p><p>算法也不会为 YouTube、TikTok 或 Instagram 创建内容，但所有这些平台在某种意义上都受到<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/how-facebooks-master-algorithm-powers-the-social-network-1508673600?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">各自内容过滤算法的</a>控制。娱乐平台仍然依赖人类观察趋势并提出原创想法并不奇怪。巴贾里亚的评论并没有涉及数据如何决定哪些人类起源的想法可以通过（正如<a href="https://netflixtechblog.com/supporting-content-decision-makers-with-machine-learning-995b7b76006f" target="_blank" class="icon none">Netflix 自己的工程师所概述的</a>那样），也没有涉及制作更多的节目和剧集。</p><h3>更紧缩的预算，更多的机器学习</h3><p>“预算变得越来越紧张，把钱花在哪里变得越来越重要，”迪恩说。 “我认为这就是 Netflix 现在比以往任何时候都更多地使用数据的原因。”</p><p> Netflix 的内容预算从去年到今年持平，约为 170 亿美元。 </p><div class="media-object scope-
          inline
"><div class="media-object-video"><div class="wsj-media-summary clearfix"><div class="strap-container"><h4 class="strap" itemprop="description"></h4></div></div><iframe width="400" height="225" src="https://video-api.wsj.com/api-video/player/v3/iframe.html?guid=0B69A51F-2148-4479-9D5B-1AB9ABE390DC&amp;height=225&amp;width=400&amp;plid=video_amp&amp;chainVideos=true&amp;parentUrl=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.wsj.com%2Famp%2Farticles%2Fhow-netflixs-algorithms-and-tech-feed-its-success-90632b92&amp;a=a" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></iframe><p class="imageCaption"> Netflix 联席首席执行官特德·萨兰多斯 (Ted Sarandos) 表示，该公司和其他流媒体平台、工作室和网络“非常致力于”与好莱坞知名演员和作家达成协议。 Photo: Chris Delmas/Agence France-Presse/Getty Images<span class="imageCredit">
        
        
        </span></p></div></div><p>Netflix 作为整个流媒体行业的领头羊，并不是唯一一家以这种方式运营的流媒体公司。竞争服务的领导者谈论了他们如何使用数据来决定生产什么。随着越来越多的流媒体服务探索<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/amazon-plans-ad-tier-for-prime-video-streaming-service-8944fe51" target="_blank" class="icon none">提供广告支持的版本</a>，收集此类数据成为强制性的，因此它们可以为广告商提供收视率信息。</p><p> <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/paramount-para-q1-earnings-report-2023-749549" target="_blank" class="icon none">现在</a>，连续剧和电影比<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/streaming-amazon-lord-of-the-rings-netflix-disney-11662064745" target="_blank" class="icon none">以往任何时候</a>都更加昂贵。正如 Netflix 自己的工程师在 2020 年关于该公司如何使用机器学习的博客文章中<a href="https://netflixtechblog.com/supporting-content-decision-makers-with-machine-learning-995b7b76006f" target="_blank" class="icon none">所解释的</a>那样，这更有理由让人工智能为委托决策提供信息。人工智能可以获取有关哪些标题与提议的标题具有可比性、预期观众规模以及在哪些地区的信息。要做到这一点，需要应用迁移学习、知识图谱和许多其他技术，这些技术现在是尖端人工智能系统的标准——例如谷歌的 Bard 和 ChatGPT——但这并不完全是好莱坞工作室推介会议的常见内容。</p><p> Netflix 为这样的人工智能提供的数据越多，它发出的结果就越好。正如我们所看到的，当今的生成人工智能中有大量数据输入，庞大的规模可以产生令人惊讶且有用的新功能。</p><p><em>欲了解更多《华尔街日报》技术分析、评论、建议和头条新闻，</em> <a href="https://www.wsj.com/newsletters?sub=55&amp;mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none"><em>请订阅我们的每周通讯</em></a><em>。</em></p><p>写信给克里斯托弗·米姆斯 (Christopher Mims)： <a href="mailto:christopher.mims@wsj.com" target="_blank" class="icon ">christopher.mims@wsj.com</a></p></section></div></main></div> ]]>;</description><pubDate> Sat, 29 Jul 2023 01:00:00 GMT</pubDate><guid ispermalink="false"> https://www.wsj.com/articles/how-netflixs-algorithms-and-tech-feed-its-success-90632b92</guid><link/> https://www.wsj.com/articles/how-netflixs-algorithms-and-tech-feed-its-success-90632b92<author><![CDATA[Christopher Mims]]></author><category> WSJ公司</category><category>世杰交易所</category><category>技术</category><category>创新</category><category>多媒体内容服务</category><category>媒体内容分发</category><category>在线服务提供商</category><category>媒体/娱乐</category><category>流媒体服务</category><category>技术</category><category>政治/一般新闻</cat